article.description: — Xavier Bishop had 18 points as Montana State stretched its win streak to eight games, easily defeating Weber State 78-57 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Bishop leads Montana St. past Weber St. 78-57
article.linkText: Bishop leads Montana St. past Weber St. 78-57
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- — Xavier Bishop had 18 points as Montana State stretched its win streak to eight games, easily defeating Weber State 78-57 on Saturday night. Jubrile Belo and Amin Adamu added 17 points apiece for the Bobcats (17-5, 9-2 Big Sky Conference), while RaeQuan Battle chipped in 15. Belo also had eight rebounds, while Adamu posted six rebounds. Seikou Sisoho Jawara had 14 points for the Wildcats (18-6, 11-2), whose eight-game win streak ended. Zahir Porter added 11 points. Koby McEwen had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
